      • getAllImportStatements

        public static List<String> getAllImportStatements()
        Return a sequence of import statements to prepare a just-instantiated Gremlin-Groovy interpreter. This includes both Tinkerpop stack and Titan symbol imports. Though intended for use in Gremlin-Groovy, the returned import statements all end with semicolons, so the statements are valid under the syntax of both Groovy and Java. This only returns import and import static statements (at least, as of the last time this comment was updated).
        Returns:
        A sequence of import statements

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
                 throws FileNotFoundException
        Write a properties file with two properties: imports and staticimports. These are set to comma-separated lists of getNonStaticImports() and getStaticImports(), respectively.
        Parameters:
        args - the file to write (stdout if unspecified)
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - shouldn't happen since we only open the target file for overwriting and never for appending
